The following issues were recently filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission: 

CRS Sirrine Inc., offering of 2.5 million common shares, via Merrill Lynch Capital Markets. 

Lafarge Corp., shelf offering of up to $250 million of debt securities. 

Southwestern Electric Power, a subsidiary of Central and South West Corp., offering of $60 million in first mortgage bonds. 

Sun Microsystems Inc., proposed offering of $125 million convertible debentures, via Goldman, Sachs & Co. 

